const en4VoiceSection = {id:'en4-voice',title:'Voice: Active and Passive',definition:'In <b>active voice</b>, the subject does the action. In <b>passive voice</b>, the object receives the action. Object becomes subject; choose the correct form of <b>be + V3</b>.',support:'মনে রাখো: Active-এর object-কে সামনে আনো, tense অনুযায়ী be বসাও, তারপর V3। কর্তা দরকার হলে by + object form।',table:{headers:['Active subject','Passive object form'],rows:voicePronouns},groups:voiceTenseData.map(([title,rule,examples])=>({title,rule,examples})),tip:'Voice বদলানোর আগে object আছে কি না দেখো। “He sleeps”–এ কোনও object নেই, তাই সাধারণ passive সম্ভব নয়।',memory:'Object আগে, be + V3; প্রয়োজনে by-এর পরে object form ধরি।',mistakes:[['The work is done by he.','The work is done by him.'],['A letter is wrote by her.','A letter is written by her.'],['The room has cleaned.','The room has been cleaned.'],['The work will completed.','The work will be completed.'],['English is teaching by him.','English is taught by him.'],['The book was being read by I.','The book was being read by me.'],['He was laughed.','He laughed. (intransitive)'],['The baby is slept.','The baby sleeps / The baby is sleeping.'],['Let the door opened.','Let the door be opened.'],['The teacher gave a prize to I.','The teacher gave a prize to me.'],['The letter has been wrote.','The letter has been written.'],['The work is being do.','The work is being done.'],['Rice is grown by people.','Rice is grown. (by-agent can be dropped)'],['The car was repaired by the mechanic yesterday.','The car was repaired by the mechanic yesterday.'],['The story was told me.','I was told the story / The story was told to me.'],['The homework is doing by Rina.','The homework is being done by Rina.'],['The room was cleaned by they.','The room was cleaned by them.'],['A new bridge will be built.','A new bridge will be built.'],['He is known to me.','He is known to me.'],['The box has been opened by the boy.','The box has been opened by the boy.']],exam:['Change voice: “They grow rice.” → <b>Rice is grown by them.</b>','Choose: “A letter ___ by Rina.” → <b>was written</b>.','Which cannot be passivised? “The baby sleeps.” → <b>no object</b>.','Choose pronoun: “The work was done by ___.” → <b>him</b>.','Choose: “The room has ___.” → <b>been cleaned</b>.']};
const en4Extras = {id:'en4-special',title:'Imperatives, two objects and by-agent',definition:'Some voice questions need a special pattern. Imperatives use <b>Let + object + be + V3</b>. With two objects, either object may become the passive subject.',support:'মনে রাখো: “Open the door” → “Let the door be opened.” আর “Give me a book” → “I am given a book” / “A book is given to me.”',groups:[{title:'Passive of imperatives: 10 examples',rule:'Use Let + object + be + V3. For negative commands use Let not + object + be + V3.',examples:['Open the door. → Let the door be opened.','Write the answer. → Let the answer be written.','Do the work. → Let the work be done.','Clean the room. → Let the room be cleaned.','Read the lesson. → Let the lesson be read.','Do not waste time. → Let not time be wasted.','Do not tell a lie. → Let not a lie be told.','Keep the door closed. → Let the door be kept closed.','Follow the rules. → Let the rules be followed.','Help the poor. → Let the poor be helped.']},{title:'Passive of SVOO sentences: 10 examples',rule:'With give, tell, show, teach, offer, send etc., make either indirect object or direct object the subject.',examples:['He gave me a pen. → I was given a pen.','He gave me a pen. → A pen was given to me.','The teacher taught us English. → We were taught English.','The teacher taught us English. → English was taught to us.','Mother told me a story. → I was told a story.','Mother told me a story. → A story was told to me.','They offered her a job. → She was offered a job.','They sent us a message. → We were sent a message.','Father bought me a bicycle. → I was bought a bicycle.','The guide showed us the way. → We were shown the way.']},{title:'When passive is impossible',rule:'Intransitive verbs do not take an object, so a normal passive cannot be made.',examples:['He sleeps. → no passive','The baby cries. → no passive','Birds fly. → no passive','The sun rises. → no passive','She arrived late. → no passive','They laughed loudly. → no passive','The child fell. → no passive','The train departed. → no passive','We walked home. → no passive','The river flows. → no passive','He died yesterday. → no passive','She smiled. → no passive','The dog barked. → no passive','Leaves fell. → no passive','The audience clapped. → no passive']},{title:'Use or drop the by-agent',rule:'Keep by + agent when it is important, unknown, surprising or needed for clarity. Drop it when the doer is obvious or unimportant.',examples:['The poem was written by Rabindranath. (keep)','The thief was arrested by the police. (often keep)','The road was repaired. (drop unknown/unimportant agent)','English is spoken in many countries. (drop general people)','The Taj Mahal was built by Shah Jahan. (keep)','The window was broken. (agent unknown)','The patient was examined by the doctor. (keep if relevant)','Rice is grown in this region. (drop general farmers)','The match was won by our team. (keep)','The classroom was cleaned. (drop)']}],tip:'Never force a by-agent. “The road was repaired by someone” is weaker than “The road was repaired” unless the person matters.',memory:'Object না থাকলে passive নয়; দুই object হলে দুই পথ হয়।',mistakes:[['Let the work done.','Let the work be done.'],['I was given a pen by he.','I was given a pen by him.'],['The baby was slept.','The baby slept.'],['A pen was given me.','A pen was given to me.'],['Let not the rules broken.','Let not the rules be broken.']],exam:['Imperative passive: “Close the gate.” → <b>Let the gate be closed.</b>.','SVOO passive: “She gave me a gift.” → <b>I was given a gift.</b>.','By-agent: “The poem was written by Tagore.” Why keep it? <b>Writer is important.</b>.']};
